Class Get

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.coveros.selenified.element.Get

  • public class Get
extends Object
    Get retrieves information about a particular element. If an object isn't present, null will be returned

    3.2.1

      • tableRows

        public Element tableRows()
        Retrieves the rows in the element. If the element isn't present or a table, a null value will be returned. The rows will be returned in one element and they can be iterated through, or selecting using the `setMatch` method
        Returns:
        List: a list of the table rows as WebElements

      • numOfTableColumns

        Integer: the number of columns the table has

      • tableRow

        public Element tableRow(int rowNum)
        Retrieves a specific row from the element. If the element isn't present or a table, or doesn't have that many rows a null value will be returned.
        Parameters:
        rowNum - - the row number of the table to obtain - note, row numbering starts at 0
        Returns:
        List: a list of the table cells in the row as WebElements

      • tableCell

        public Element tableCell(int rowNum,
                         int colNum)
        Retrieves a specific cell from the element. If the element isn't present or a table, or the row and cell combination doesn't exist, a null value will be returned.
        Parameters:
        rowNum - - the number of the row in the table - note, row numbering starts at 0
        colNum - - the number of the column in the table - note, column numbering starts at 0
        Returns:
        WebElement: the cell element object, and all associated values with it
